text: I had not seen the first movie but I am aware that Point Break  with Luke Bracey is a remake yet he  not only mesmerized me with his fearlessness but he actually get me interested with Osaka 8. Somehow, in his own way, he was able to reach out to me and made me aware how nature can sometimes brings one being to a level of intensity that might not be for everyone to understand, but everybody can actually relate if one would just for a minute, view nature with complete abandon and embrace the very essence of being one with it. Hahahaha.. I know it is kind of weird, but the film somehow makes me wish Osaka 8 is not just fiction. It made me marvel of the attention the film makers place on the cinematography to evoke raw emotions from me about nature & the forces with it and towards Luke Bracey 's sentiment on this film hahahaha..I say for me he is very effective on this film. Not everyone may agree, but then again aint we all entitled to our own opinion?:)
